        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>, Wednesday, Section
                Taberoth.<lb/> (c. <date>November</date>) <date>5613</date></p>
            <p>To my dear etc. etc.——</p>
            <p>Sir,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Mr. <persName>Henry Goldsmith</persName> has no more
                prayer–books<lb/> for they have all been sold by me, and I paid him<lb/> for every
                thing I had taken from him. Last week he<lb/> showed me a letter from you that you
                want to give<lb/> him prayer–books, unbound, at $1.50. Therefore,<lb/> please let me
                know whether you would send me<lb/> some prayer–books unbound, and three sets
                of<lb/> Pentateuch unbound, and one Sephardic holi–<lb/>day book. If you are in
                doubt about the paymen<add>t</add><lb/> you may write to <persName>Mr.
                    Goldsmith</persName> who will tell<lb/> you the truth. For, thank God,
                everything I buy<lb/> and every thing I do under the sun, is done<lb/> honorably.
                You may be sure that whatever I<lb/> sell, I shall give the money to
                    <persName>Goldsmith</persName>, or send it<lb/> to you. But you do as you
                please, since for two<lb/> years now I have been buying from
                    <persName>Goldsmith</persName>, and<lb/> paying for everything. If you desire
                guarantees<lb/> you may write to <persName>Goldsmith</persName>.<lb/> Your servant<lb/>
                <persName role="author">Simon Cohen Noht</persName>
                <lb/> We may send more, or, less 20<lb/>
            </p>
        </body>
